The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically boundary labeling for rectangular diagrams. The problem involves connecting points inside a rectangle to points on its boundary with axis-aligned polylines with few bends, and minimizing the total length of the leaders. This falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses algorithms and complexity, which suggests it could also belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem involves graph drawing, which could place it in the category of graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses aesthetics and optimization, which could place it in the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
